write_generali...feedthru_paths(25.10)  write_generali...feedthru_paths(25.10)

Name
       write_generalized_feedthru_paths  -  Automatically  derives feedthrough
       topological paths from the user specified paths to cover all the  chain
       connectivity probabilities in a master and clone hinst scenario

Syntax
       write_generalized_feedthru_paths

       [-help]

       [-dont_generalize_reverse_paths]

       [-dont_generalize_sub_paths]

       [-topological_out_file <file_name>]

       -use_topological_file <file_name>

       Automatically derives feedthrough topological paths from the user spec-
       ified paths to cover all the chain connectivity probabilities in a mas-
       ter  and  clone  hinst scenario. It reads an input topological file, in
       version 0.5 and creates the version 2.0 topological file.

       Note: For the given set of master-clone hinst  connectivity,  based  on
       floorplan,  multiple  user defined paths may be required for other same
       set hinst master and clones. The write_generalized_feedthru_paths  com-
       mand  can  automatically  choose correct path for individual master and
       clone hinst, based on matching connectivity and floorplan, from the set
       of paths provided by the user.

Parameters
       -dont_generalize_reverse_paths
              When enabled, the generalization algorithm does  not  generalize
              reverse chain paths.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -dont_generalize_sub_paths
              When  enabled,  the generalization algorithm does not generalize
              sub-paths.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each write_generalized_feedthru_paths parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man write_generalized_feedthru_paths

       -topological_out_file <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the output topo 2.0 file that contains all
              paths for all master and clone chain.

              Note:  This  file  should  be  used as an input file for the in-
              sertPtnFeedthrough command.

              Default: path.topo

              Data_type: string, optional

       -use_topological_file <file_name>
              Specifies the user specified feedthrough path guidance file. The
              input topological file with new version 0.5  format  contains  a
              path for one master and clone chain to derive path of all master
              and clone chains.

              Note:  You  can  use  the  Path  Guidance  GUI form (Partition -
              Feedthough Ports - Path Guidance) to  generate  the  topological
              file with new version 0.5 format.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
              * The following command reads the topology file "a.topo" in ver-
                sion   0.5  and  creates  the  version  2.0  topological  file
                "path.topo":

                write_generalized_feedthru_paths  -use_topological_file a.topo

              * The following command reads the topological file  "a.topo"  in
                version  0.5  and  creates  the  version  2.0 topological file
                "new.topo":

                write_generalized_feedthru_paths  -use_topological_file a.topo
                -topological_out_file new.topo

Related Information
